  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 7$$, $$Lesson 2$$, $$trap$$, $$to catch and hold something (or someone) so it cannot escape$$, $$/træp/$$, $$The clever plant can trap little flies inside its leaves.$$, $$困住；诱捕$$),
  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 7$$, $$Lesson 2$$, $$sticky$$, $$having a substance (such as glue or honey) on it that things easily attach to: covered in a substance that things stick to$$, $$/ˈstɪki/$$, $$My fingers got really sticky after eating the honey toast.$$, $$黏的；黏糊糊的$$),
  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 7$$, $$Lesson 2$$, $$climate$$, $$the regular pattern of weather conditions of a particular place$$, $$/ˈklaɪmət/$$, $$The jungle has a warm and wet climate all year round.$$, $$气候$$),
