  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 8$$, $$Lesson 1$$, $$cover$$, $$to place something over or in front of something in order to hide, protect or decorate it$$, $$/ˈkʌvə/$$, $$She used a blanket to cover the puppy when it was cold.$$, $$盖；遮盖；覆盖$$),
