  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 8$$, $$Lesson 1$$, $$landfill$$, $$an area where waste is buried under the ground$$, $$/ˈlændfɪl/$$, $$Too much plastic from our city ends up in the landfill.$$, $$垃圾填埋场$$),
  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 8$$, $$Lesson 1$$, $$cardboard$$, $$a stiff and thick kind of paper that is used especially for making boxes$$, $$/ˈkɑːdbɔːd/$$, $$We built a cool spaceship from an old cardboard box.$$, $$硬纸板；卡纸$$),
  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 8$$, $$Lesson 1$$, $$environmental$$, $$connected with the natural conditions in which people, animals and plants live; connected with the environment$$, $$/ɪnˌvaɪrənˈmentl/$$, $$Our class joined an environmental project to clean the park.$$, $$环境的；有关环境的$$),
  ($$4B$$, $$Unit 8$$, $$Lesson 1$$, $$electronics$$, $$devices (such as televisions, radios, and computers) that operate using many small electrical parts$$, $$/ɪˌlekˈtrɒnɪks/$$, $$Please don't throw old electronics into the rubbish bin.$$, $$电子设备；电子产品$$),
